Bennett Oghifo CRC Credit Bureau Limited, a credit reporting firm, has launched a mobile app to help individuals quickly and easily know what their credit score is. Financial institutions make use of credit scores to determine who qualifies for a loan. The company stated that with the new mobile app, CRC Mobile, individuals now have access to their credit information and credit scores through their mobile phones. The CRC Mobile App is available for immediate download on the Google and Apple Play stores. The CRC Mobile Application was formally launched at CRC Credit Bureauâ€™s Tenth Anniversary celebrations last December, with an introductory video that showcased its different features and how it can be used to subscribe to the various credit monitoring products /services that CRC has to offer including its CRC Score and CRC Self Enquiry Credit reports. The Managing Director/CEO of CRC Credit Bureau Limited, Tunde Popoola, said the launch of the mobile application was one of the innovations that the company has created to enable consumers in Nigeria and diaspora access information that empowers them to take control of their financial reputation and be better informed. Prior to taking a loan, they can also monitor their exposures for accurate reporting and the reduction of identity fraud. CRC Credit Bureau has 13 products and services that are all available on the mobile application CRC Mobile.